T1  - Harassment Based on Sex: Protecting Social Status in the Context of Gender Hierarchy
AU  - Berdahl, Jennifer L.
Y1  - 2007/04/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2007.24351879
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2007.24351879
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 641
EP  - 658
VL  - 32
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - I conceptualize sex-based harassment as behavior that derogates an individual based on sex. I propose that sex-based harassment is fundamentally motivated by the harasser's desire to protect or enhance his or her own sex-based status, a desire that stems from the fact that social status is stratified by a system of gender hierarchy. This theory explains currently identified forms of sexual harassment and predicts others, including nonsexual harassment between women.
AB  - I conceptualize sex-based harassment as behavior that derogates an individual based on sex. I propose that sex-based harassment is fundamentally motivated by the harasser's desire to protect or enhance his or her own sex-based status, a desire that stems from the fact that social status is stratified by a system of gender hierarchy. This theory explains currently identified forms of sexual harassment and predicts others, including nonsexual harassment between women.
